negrohead
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A tobacco type; NZ use common in early colonial days and as a common payment to a trade with the Maoris; also smoked by early settlers, sailors, stationhands etc.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: negro head, negro-head
