Date: 24/11/1847
Source: Letters to His Father, 1843-1851
Author: CHAPMAN
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: The proper way to arrange a blanket for the bush is to sew it up like a sack. As to food you carry what you like; and what the host always furnishes is tea (at every meal), damper, i.e. a sort of dough cake baked in the ashes, very good if well made; and fried pork. He can generally furnishthe traveller with a short black pipe and some `negro-head' or Cavendish.
Notes: 1847 Nov 24 H.S. Chapman Letters to His Father  [TS,ATB] in 1958 Miller Early Victorian NZ 140

